<article>
    <h1>MUSH&#xAD;ROOM STROGANOFF IN&#xAD;GRE&#xAD;DI&#xAD;ENTS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201209/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-09"><time>2020-12-09</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | LIVING WELL</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>2 Quorn ve­gan fil­lets</p>
    <p>15ml veg­etable oil</p>
    <p>1 large onion, finely chopped</p>
    <p>3 gar­lic cloves, finely chopped</p>
    <p>250g brown or white but­ton mush­rooms, cut into halves or quar­ters (but not too small as they will shrink when cook­ing)</p>
    <p>50g cashews</p>
    <p>1 Tbs ap­ple cider vine­gar</p>
    <p>2 Tbs of nu­tri­tional yeast</p>
    <p>180ml wa­ter</p>
    <p>300ml ve­gan broth</p>
    <p>30g fresh pars­ley</p>
    <p>1 Tbs of mus­tard pow­der</p>
    <p>A pinch of salt and pep­per</p>
    <p>METHOD</p>
    <p>1. Pan-fry the Quorn fil­lets on both sides. When cool, cut them into bite-size pieces.</p>
    <p>2. Heat oil in a large saucepan, add the onion and gar­lic. 3. Fry onion and gar­lic un­til translu­cent. Then, add the mush­rooms and bite-size Quorn fil­lets and fry for an­other six to seven min­utes.</p>
    <p>4. Mean­while, pre­pare the sour cream by blend­ing the cashews, ap­ple cider vine­gar, nu­tri­tional yeast and wa­ter in a blender.</p>
    <p>6. Add the sour cream and ve­gan broth to the fry­ing pan. Bring to a gen­tle boil.</p>
    <p>7. Add most of the pars­ley, mus­tard pow­der, salt and pep­per and let it sim­mer for a fur­ther 10 min­utes. 8. Gar­nish with the re­main­ing pars­ley and serve im­me­di­ately with pasta, rice or buck­wheat noo­dles.</p>
    <p>Serves five</p>

